nz.wicker.bmad.matrix

Class BooleanMatrix

  • java.lang.Object
    • nz.wicker.bmad.matrix.BooleanMatrix

  • public class BooleanMatrix
extends Object
    Dense boolean matrix with 3-valued boolean logic TRUE is represented as 2, UNKNOWN is represented as 1, FALSE is represented as 0, AND corresponds to MIN, OR corresponds to MAX

      • relativeOneZeroZeroOneReconstructionError

        public Tuple<Double,Double> relativeOneZeroZeroOneReconstructionError(BooleanMatrix reconstruction,
                                                                      double onesWeight)
        Calculates the relative 1->0 and 0->1 reconstruction error, that is, the total error divided by total maximum possible error. Assumes, that there are no unknowns in the reconstruction. The total weight equals #0 + onesWeight * #1. Each 1->0 error costs onesWeight. Each 0->1 error costs 1.
        Parameters:
        reconstruction -
        onesWeight -
        Returns:
        tuple with relative 1->0 and 0->1 errors

      • combineVectors

        public BooleanMatrix combineVectors(Tuple<ArrayList<Integer>,HashMap<Integer,Set<Integer>>> pair,
                                    boolean combineRow)
        Takes in a Tuple, HashMap>> which is two ways of representing the same duplication info of the same occurrence. and a boolean flag (true = combine row, false = combine cols).
        Parameters:
        pair: - Tuple, HashMap>> which is two ways of representing the same duplication info: Tuple._1: the indices of all rows/cols to be removed. Tuple._2: keys = first occurrence, vals = all duplications (to be removed) of the item indexed by the key.
        combineRow: - if true, remove all rows whose index is in Tuple._1, otherwise remove indexed cols.
